Malaysia Raises Property Gains Tax to 10% if Sold Within 2 Years

-- B y   E l f f i e   C h e w   a n d   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 
2011-10-07T08:54:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-07/malaysia-raises-property-gains-tax-to-10-if-sold-within-2-years.html
Malaysia will raise the capital gains
tax to 10 percent on property sold within two years to help rein
in prices and bolster government finances, Prime Minister Najib
Razak said in his budget speech at parliament in  Kuala Lumpur 
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Elffie Chew at 
